<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="sit-v">sit <strong><em>v</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /sɪt/    美 /sɪt/  </p>
<p>(sat, sat)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>(使) 坐；(使) 就座：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>sit on / in a chair
坐在椅子上</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>sit at the table
坐在桌子旁</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>Sit down</strong>, please!
请坐！</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The mother sat the child at a little table.
母亲帮孩子在小桌旁坐好。</p></div>

<h3 id="seat-sit">辨析 seat, sit</h3>
<p><strong>seat ** 为及物动词，意为“使坐下”，“使就座”。
</strong>sit ** 为不及物动词，意为“坐下”。</p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Jean sat at the table writing a letter. 
琼坐在桌旁写信。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.<strong>坐落；被安放：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The city <strong>sits on</strong> a hill.
这座城市坐落在山上。</p></div>

<h4 id="3">3.<strong>可供...坐：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The car will sit six people.
这辆车可坐6人。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="sit-up">sit up</h3>
<p>1.<strong>坐起来；坐直；熬夜：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>If burns are on the face, the victim should sit up. 
如果脸部烧伤，伤员应该坐直。</p><footer>人教⑤ – 5</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>We sat up late watching a movie. 
我们熬夜看了场电影。</p></div></div>